	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><hi rend="underline">&#36;40 Enclosed</hi>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>202 St. Paul Street</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>Aug. 24th&#47;54</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I returned<lb/> from <placeName>New York</placeName> on <date>Monday</date> and<lb/> found your note of <date>3d</date> inst. with<lb/> an enclosed for <persName>Mr. De Sola</persName>&#44; which<lb/> was delivered.  Accept my heart&#45;<lb/>felt thanks for your kindness.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I leave another favour to ask of<lb/> you&#44; which I am confident you will<lb/> kindly execute for me.  While<lb/> a Prisoner at <placeName>Wilmington</placeName> I had<lb/> occasion to borrow some money<lb/> on a <hi rend="underline">diamond ring</hi> from a <hi rend="underline"><lb/><persName>Mr.Raw</persName></hi>&#44; who keeps a clothing store<lb/> in <placeName>Wilmington</placeName> on <placeName>Market Street near<lb/> 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi></placeName>.  He loaned me &#36;20&#44; for which<lb/> I promised to pay him &#36;23.  He<lb/> gave me a receipt for the ring&#44; which<lb/> I forwarded to <persName>Mr. Frankel</persName>.  <persName>Mr. F.</persName><lb/> has promised to get me the ring&#44; ac&#45;<lb/>cording to the enclosed letter.  I also<lb/> owe <persName>Mr. Frankel</persName> &#36;15 which he kind&#45;<lb/>ly loaned me.  I therefore enclose</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>you &#36;40. in order that you may<lb/> pay <persName>Mr. Frankel</persName> &#36;15 and give<lb/> <persName>Mr. F.</persName> &#36;23 to get the ring and &#36;20<lb/> for expense to <placeName>Wilmington</placeName> &#38; return&#44;<lb/> and pay Express on ring to <placeName><hi rend="underline">N. York</hi></placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The ring is a single stone <hi rend="underline">pure first</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">water diamond</hi> ladies ring&#44; chased<lb/> gold.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please send the ring to <placeName><hi rend="underline">New York</hi></placeName><lb/> by Express addressed to me&#44; and<lb/> marked &#8220;to be called for&#8221;.  <hi rend="underline">Please</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">advise me of having sent it</hi> by <hi rend="underline">ad</hi>&#45;<lb/><hi rend="underline">dressing</hi> me to <placeName><hi rend="underline">Earles Hotel N. Y.</hi></placeName><lb/> where I shall be by <date>Monday</date> next.<lb/>  I hope you will be able to forward<lb/> it by that time as my wife will<lb/> be waiting for it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With great respect and esteem</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours Most Gratefully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">C. M. De La Mar</persName></hi></p>
				<p><persName>Mr. Frankel</persName> or his partner has the order for the<lb/> ring.  Write me to <placeName>Earles Hotel N.Y.</placeName><lb/> and mark letter &#8220;<hi rend="underline">To be called for</hi>&#8221;</p>
		</body>
